On July 22, 2016, the President signed four bills into law. The first bill, H.R. 4875, establishes the United States Semiquincentennial Commission to plan and coordinate the commemoration of the history of the United States leading up to its 250th anniversary. The second bill, H.R. 5588, provides a cost-of-living adjustment for the beneficiaries of veterans' disability compensation and dependency and indemnity compensation. The third bill, S. 524, addresses prescription opioid abuse and addiction by authorizing grant programs for prevention and education, expanding access to treatment and recovery options, and providing resources to veterans, women, and children. The fourth bill, S. 2840, expands the allowable use of grant funds awarded through the Office of Community Oriented Policing Services to include participation in active shooter training programs.